ZH: 我们不希望再次打仗。
EN: We do not want to go to war again.
ZH: 这个国家已经打过两次仗。
EN: This country has already fought two wars.
ZH: 他们决定要打一仗来保护自己的领土。
EN: They decided to fight a war to protect their territory.
ZH: 那个将军在战场上打了多次仗。
EN: That general has fought many battles on the battlefield.
ZH: 他的爷爷曾经在抗日战争中打过仗。
EN: His grandfather fought in the war against Japan.
ZH: 战争带来了太多的伤亡和毁坏。
EN: War has brought too much casualties and destruction.
ZH: 在电影中，他们使用最新的武器打仗。
EN: In the movie, they use the latest weapons to fight.
ZH: 在过去，人们使用弓箭和刀剑打仗。
EN: In the past, people fought with bows and swords.
ZH: 她在战争中失去了许多亲人。
EN: She lost many relatives in the war.
ZH: 这支军队已经准备好打一场正义的仗。
EN: This army is ready to fight a just war.
ZH: 我们需要媒体报道更多关于战争的真相。
EN: We need the media to report more about the truth of war.
ZH: 战争是人类历史上最可怕的事情之一。
EN: War is one of the most terrible things in human history.
ZH: 在战争中，士兵经常会面临生命危险。
EN: Soldiers often face life-threatening situations in war.
ZH: 他在国外打仗已经好几年了。
EN: He has been fighting overseas for several years.
ZH: 孩子们在玩模拟战争游戏。
EN: The kids are playing a simulation war game.
ZH: 这次冲突升级为真正的战争了。
EN: This conflict has escalated into a real war.
ZH: 为了和平，我们必须避免打仗。
EN: We must avoid war in order to achieve peace.
ZH: 战争并不会解决问题，只会造成更多的伤害。
EN: War does not solve problems, it only causes more harm.
ZH: 他下定决心要为国家打一场胜仗。
EN: He is determined to win a victory for the country.
ZH: 在战争中，孩子们失去了正常的童年。
EN: In war, children lose their normal childhood.
